1
01:00:00,033 --> 01:00:03,833
<b>On June 16th 2014, a farmer from Virginia</b>

2
01:00:03,833 --> 01:00:06,033
<b>named Jeremiah Heaton planted</b>

3
01:00:06,033 --> 01:00:07,566
<b>a flag in the African desert.</b>

4
01:00:08,400 --> 01:00:10,300
<b>Why? To make his 7 year old</b>

5
01:00:10,300 --> 01:00:11,866
<b>daughter Emily a princess.</b>

6
01:00:12,766 --> 01:00:15,533
<b>He claimed 800 square miles of land</b>

7
01:00:15,533 --> 01:00:18,300
<b>between Egypt and Sudan and called it the</b>

8
01:00:18,300 --> 01:00:19,566
<b>Kingdom of North Sudan.</b>

9
01:00:20,533 --> 01:00:22,933
<b>CNN, Time, Newsweek,</b>

10
01:00:23,666 --> 01:00:25,666
<b>hundreds of outlets covered it.</b>

11
01:00:25,766 --> 01:00:26,933
<b>Most of them treated it like</b>

12
01:00:26,933 --> 01:00:28,533
<b>a cute human interest story.</b>

13
01:00:29,066 --> 01:00:30,166
<b>But here's what almost</b>

14
01:00:30,166 --> 01:00:32,800
<b>nobody explained. He wasn't crazy.</b>

15
01:00:33,366 --> 01:00:35,400
<b>This was one of the only places on earth</b>

16
01:00:35,400 --> 01:00:37,633
<b>besides Antarctica where you could even</b>

17
01:00:37,633 --> 01:00:39,233
<b>try something like this.</b>

18
01:00:39,666 --> 01:00:41,366
<b>Because Berthawil is one of the only</b>

19
01:00:41,366 --> 01:00:42,699
<b>pieces of habitable land</b>

20
01:00:42,699 --> 01:00:44,066
<b>that no country claims.</b>

21
01:00:44,733 --> 01:00:47,633
<b>This isn't a disputed territory, it's not</b>

22
01:00:47,633 --> 01:00:48,866
<b>a border conflict where</b>

23
01:00:48,866 --> 01:00:50,666
<b>both sides claim the same land.</b>

24
01:00:51,366 --> 01:00:53,633
<b>This is the opposite. Both Egypt and</b>

25
01:00:53,633 --> 01:00:55,666
<b>Sudan actively reject it.</b>

26
01:00:56,033 --> 01:00:58,466
<b>And here's the kicker, claiming Berthawil</b>

27
01:00:58,466 --> 01:01:01,000
<b>would cost either Egypt or Sudan the land</b>

28
01:01:01,000 --> 01:01:02,933
<b>that they actually want next door.</b>

29
01:01:03,699 --> 01:01:04,566
<b>There's two pieces of</b>

30
01:01:04,566 --> 01:01:06,166
<b>land between Egypt and Sudan.</b>

31
01:01:07,033 --> 01:01:09,733
<b>Berthawil, 800 square miles of landlocked</b>

32
01:01:09,733 --> 01:01:12,433
<b>desert, no water, no infrastructure,</b>

33
01:01:13,166 --> 01:01:14,433
<b>economically worthless</b>

34
01:01:14,433 --> 01:01:16,300
<b>compared to Hala'ip and...</b>

35
01:01:16,933 --> 01:01:20,133
<b>The Hala'ip triangle, 8000 square miles,</b>

36
01:01:20,466 --> 01:01:22,633
<b>10 times bigger with the Red Sea</b>

37
01:01:22,633 --> 01:01:24,466
<b>coastline and oil potential.</b>

38
01:01:25,066 --> 01:01:26,266
<b>And on top of that,</b>

39
01:01:26,266 --> 01:01:28,800
<b>700,000 tons of manganese.</b>

40
01:01:29,466 --> 01:01:32,033
<b>And here's the problem, because of how</b>

41
01:01:32,033 --> 01:01:32,966
<b>the British drew the</b>

42
01:01:32,966 --> 01:01:35,166
<b>borders, you can't claim both.</b>

43
01:01:35,933 --> 01:01:39,133
<b>In 1899, Britain and Egypt signed the</b>

44
01:01:39,133 --> 01:01:41,366
<b>Anglo-Egyptian Condominium Agreement.</b>

45
01:01:41,866 --> 01:01:44,166
<b>The treaty says Sudan is defined as</b>

46
01:01:44,166 --> 01:01:45,533
<b>territory south of the</b>

47
01:01:45,533 --> 01:01:47,966
<b>22nd parallel of latitude.</b>

48
01:01:48,366 --> 01:01:50,800
<b>Quite straightforward. A straight line</b>

49
01:01:50,800 --> 01:01:53,666
<b>across the map at the 22nd parallel.</b>

50
01:01:54,033 --> 01:01:56,866
<b>Under this border, Egypt gets Hala'ip and</b>

51
01:01:56,866 --> 01:01:58,466
<b>Sudan gets Berthawil.</b>

52
01:01:58,966 --> 01:02:00,466
<b>But three years later, the British</b>

53
01:02:00,466 --> 01:02:01,800
<b>changed their minds.</b>

54
01:02:02,599 --> 01:02:06,000
<b>On November the 4th, 1902, they created a</b>

55
01:02:06,000 --> 01:02:07,433
<b>new administrative boundary.</b>

56
01:02:08,033 --> 01:02:10,699
<b>Not a straight line this time. This one</b>

57
01:02:10,699 --> 01:02:12,500
<b>was based on tribal use</b>

58
01:02:12,500 --> 01:02:13,933
<b>and settlement patterns.</b>

59
01:02:14,466 --> 01:02:17,566
<b>The Ababdah tribe graced in Berthawil, so</b>

60
01:02:17,566 --> 01:02:18,666
<b>Britain assigned it to</b>

61
01:02:18,666 --> 01:02:19,900
<b>Egyptian administration.</b>

62
01:02:20,666 --> 01:02:23,133
<b>The Beja tribes in Hala'ip were tied to</b>

63
01:02:23,133 --> 01:02:24,866
<b>Sudan, so they assigned that</b>

64
01:02:24,866 --> 01:02:26,199
<b>to Sudanese administration.</b>

65
01:02:27,233 --> 01:02:30,500
<b>Now, here's the problem. Two borders and</b>

66
01:02:30,500 --> 01:02:32,099
<b>two completely different outcomes.</b>

67
01:02:32,633 --> 01:02:35,533
<b>The 1899 border gives Egypt</b>

68
01:02:35,533 --> 01:02:37,699
<b>Hala'ip the valuable coastline.</b>

69
01:02:38,266 --> 01:02:41,266
<b>The 1902 border gives Sudan the Hala'ip.</b>

70
01:02:41,699 --> 01:02:44,733
<b>Both countries want Hala'ip, so Egypt</b>

71
01:02:44,733 --> 01:02:46,666
<b>claims the 1899 line.</b>

72
01:02:47,266 --> 01:02:50,166
<b>Sudan claims the 1902 line. And</b>

73
01:02:50,166 --> 01:02:52,866
<b>Berthawil? Neither will touch</b>

74
01:02:52,866 --> 01:02:55,033
<b>it, because claiming Berthawil</b>

75
01:02:55,366 --> 01:02:56,466
<b>means accepting the</b>

76
01:02:56,466 --> 01:02:58,699
<b>border that gives away Hala'ip.</b>

77
01:02:58,866 --> 01:03:00,433
<b>That's why Jeremiah Heaton</b>

78
01:03:00,433 --> 01:03:02,033
<b>could just walk right in.</b>

79
01:03:02,733 --> 01:03:06,233
<b>Two colonial borders. One paradox still</b>

80
01:03:06,233 --> 01:03:09,133
<b>unresolved 70 years after independence.</b>

81
01:03:10,333 --> 01:03:11,866
<b>So why don't they just</b>

82
01:03:11,866 --> 01:03:14,199
<b>negotiate? The Hala'ip triangle.</b>

83
01:03:14,800 --> 01:03:17,400
<b>8,000 square miles. Red Sea coastline</b>

84
01:03:17,400 --> 01:03:19,866
<b>with manganese and possible oil.</b>

85
01:03:20,333 --> 01:03:23,633
<b>In comparison, Berthawil has 800 square</b>

86
01:03:23,633 --> 01:03:25,433
<b>miles of sand and no water.</b>

87
01:03:26,000 --> 01:03:28,433
<b>One is worth fighting for, the other</b>

88
01:03:28,433 --> 01:03:30,066
<b>isn't. Egypt and Sudan</b>

89
