<b>both call it uninhabited.</b>

90
01:03:32,433 --> 01:03:34,133
<b>Tell that to the thousands running</b>

91
01:03:34,133 --> 01:03:35,666
<b>illegal gold mines there,</b>

92
01:03:35,900 --> 01:03:38,366
<b>or the Ababda tribe who've</b>

93
01:03:38,366 --> 01:03:39,900
<b>graced here for generations.</b>

94
01:03:40,800 --> 01:03:43,233
<b>No permanent settlements, no</b>

95
01:03:43,233 --> 01:03:45,166
<b>infrastructure, no government</b>

96
01:03:45,166 --> 01:03:47,466
<b>services, but it's not empty.</b>

97
01:03:48,133 --> 01:03:51,366
<b>And the Ababda? They weren't consulted in</b>

98
01:03:51,366 --> 01:03:54,333
<b>1899. They weren't consulted in 1902.</b>

99
01:03:55,066 --> 01:03:57,199
<b>Their grazing lands just became a</b>

100
01:03:57,199 --> 01:03:59,033
<b>bargaining chip between two governments</b>

101
01:03:59,033 --> 01:04:00,266
<b>that don't want them.</b>

102
01:04:00,733 --> 01:04:01,666
<b>And the dispute over</b>

103
01:04:01,666 --> 01:04:03,533
<b>Hala'ip? It's gotten violent.</b>

104
01:04:04,266 --> 01:04:07,066
<b>In 1992, Sudan granted offshore</b>

105
01:04:07,066 --> 01:04:08,433
<b>exploration rights to</b>

106
01:04:08,433 --> 01:04:09,833
<b>a Canadian oil company.</b>

107
01:04:10,400 --> 01:04:14,233
<b>Egypt objected. In 1994, Egyptian</b>

108
01:04:14,233 --> 01:04:16,266
<b>military forces expelled Sudanese</b>

109
01:04:16,266 --> 01:04:17,766
<b>officials from Hala'ip.</b>

110
01:04:18,433 --> 01:04:20,933
<b>In 1995, there was an assassination</b>

111
01:04:20,933 --> 01:04:23,000
<b>attempt on Egyptian President Mubarak.</b>

112
01:04:23,766 --> 01:04:25,733
<b>Egypt blamed Sudan and strengthened</b>

113
01:04:25,733 --> 01:04:27,566
<b>military control over Hala'ip.</b>

114
01:04:28,433 --> 01:04:31,833
<b>By 2000, Sudan withdrew its forces. Egypt</b>

115
01:04:31,833 --> 01:04:33,900
<b>has controlled the territory ever since.</b>

116
01:04:34,633 --> 01:04:36,300
<b>So when Hinton showed up to claim</b>

117
01:04:36,300 --> 01:04:38,633
<b>Berthawil, neither country cared.</b>

118
01:04:39,300 --> 01:04:40,966
<b>His daughter had asked if</b>

119
01:04:40,966 --> 01:04:42,266
<b>she could be a real princess.</b>

120
01:04:42,666 --> 01:04:44,966
<b>In Hinton's own words, "Ain't nothing</b>

121
01:04:44,966 --> 01:04:46,066
<b>more important than my</b>

122
01:04:46,066 --> 01:04:47,066
<b>daughter's happiness,</b>

123
01:04:47,066 --> 01:04:48,333
<b>and now she's got</b>

124
01:04:48,333 --> 01:04:49,666
<b>everything she ever wanted."</b>

125
01:04:50,333 --> 01:04:51,599
<b>He even got permission</b>

126
01:04:51,599 --> 01:04:53,366
<b>from Cairo to make the trip.</b>

127
01:04:53,933 --> 01:04:56,466
<b>Egypt let him drive through, plant his</b>

128
01:04:56,466 --> 01:04:59,166
<b>flag, declare the Kingdom of North Sudan.</b>

129
01:04:59,900 --> 01:05:01,033
<b>Why? Because Egypt</b>

130
01:05:01,033 --> 01:05:02,433
<b>doesn't claim Berthawil.</b>

131
01:05:02,800 --> 01:05:04,033
<b>Letting some American play</b>

132
01:05:04,033 --> 01:05:06,166
<b>pretend costs them nothing.</b>

133
01:05:06,666 --> 01:05:09,599
<b>And he's not alone. Many others have</b>

134
01:05:09,599 --> 01:05:11,233
<b>tried to claim Berthawil.</b>

135
01:05:12,033 --> 01:05:14,733
<b>A Russian radio operator declared it the</b>

136
01:05:14,733 --> 01:05:17,033
<b>Kingdom of Middle-Earth in 2017.</b>

137
01:05:17,666 --> 01:05:19,433
<b>An Indian businessman called</b>

138
01:05:19,433 --> 01:05:22,500
<b>it Kingdom of Dixit in 2017.</b>

139
01:05:23,066 --> 01:05:25,133
<b>Each one with flags, GPS</b>

140
01:05:25,133 --> 01:05:27,033
<b>locks, and bold declarations.</b>

141
01:05:28,366 --> 01:05:30,033
<b>Every claim has been ignored.</b>

142
01:05:30,333 --> 01:05:32,433
<b>The United Nations hasn't recognized any</b>

143
01:05:32,433 --> 01:05:34,666
<b>claimant as Berthawil's legitimate ruler.</b>

144
01:05:35,400 --> 01:05:38,133
<b>Because in modern international law, you</b>

145
01:05:38,133 --> 01:05:39,433
