<b>for political sovereignty,</b>

185
01:07:02,066 --> 01:07:03,566
<b>and then another border for tribal</b>

186
01:07:03,566 --> 01:07:05,833
<b>administration three years later.</b>

187
01:07:06,133 --> 01:07:07,966
<b>They didn't think about what would happen</b>

188
01:07:07,966 --> 01:07:10,133
<b>when Egypt and Sudan became independent.</b>

189
01:07:10,666 --> 01:07:11,866
<b>And the consequences are</b>

190
01:07:11,866 --> 01:07:13,166
<b>still playing out today.</b>

191
01:07:14,233 --> 01:07:17,000
<b>Egypt controls Khalaib by military force.</b>

192
01:07:17,733 --> 01:07:19,466
<b>Sudan still claims it diplomatically.</b>

193
01:07:20,099 --> 01:07:23,433
<b>A 2020 Carnegie Endowment report found</b>

194
01:07:23,433 --> 01:07:26,400
<b>that since Sudan's independence in 1956,</b>

195
01:07:27,166 --> 01:07:29,199
<b>border relations with Egypt have been</b>

196
01:07:29,199 --> 01:07:31,666
<b>characterized more by mutual suspicion</b>

197
01:07:31,666 --> 01:07:33,366
<b>than by peaceful exchange.</b>

198
01:07:34,466 --> 01:07:37,199
<b>And Berthawil is still unclaimed.</b>

199
01:07:37,833 --> 01:07:38,333
<b>Still unwanted.</b>

200
01:07:38,966 --> 01:07:41,266
<b>A colonial leftover that nobody wants to</b>

201
